title: A New Day

title: Seashell Morning
author: danae
text: almost every summer,   i look for seashells on the beach.  every morning mom whisperly yells,  â“hey…you want to go with me to search for new shells?â”  some mornings i remain in bed and just sleep,   later to hear her tell of all the smells and the beautiful seashells!  but at least once each year,  i wake up with bells to go in search of a most marvelous shell!  i walk to the shore with mom and dad… hoping to find at least one shell,  unique and rad!  we walk along the sandy shore…in some parts not so smooth,  and others more so.  it is there i might find a rolling,  drifting,  or sliding treasure…  something white and sandy? something smooth or spiky? something in the shape of a seal or a mouse or a dragon? something sure to have been home to a sea inhabitant.   oh,  what will i,  what will i,  what will i find? whatever it is,  iâ’ll keep it in my pocket and make it mine.  iâ’ll show the others and weâ’ll have a vote… who found the most unique shell to tote?

title: Seashells
author: danae
text:
seashells
\n seashells, seashells all over the beach. i think iâ’d like one of each! seashells, seashells stuck in the sand. iâ’ll save a couple in my hand. seashells, seashells rolling along with the tide. i bet itâ’s a marvelous ride! seashells, seashells smooth, bumpy, spiky, or lumpy. in all shapes and sizes… in all shades and hues… sandy, pearly, and artistically formed. seashells, seashells perhaps a home to a deep-sea creature. i love how each cell holds the smell of the beach! seashells, seashells rolling, tumbling, sliding… iâ’ll never stop admiring.

title: The Funny Bunny
author: david
